1.00	It_Serves_You_Right_to_Suffer	It Serves You Right to Suffer	It Serves You Right to Suffer is an album by blues singer, songwriter, and guitarist John Lee Hooker, released on the Impulse Records label in early 1966 (catalogue no. 9103). It was part of the short-lived Impulse folk music division, with the slogan adapted from their jazz promotion, "the new wave of folk is on Impulse!"	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/db/It_Serves_You_Right_to_Suffer.jpeg/220px-It_Serves_You_Right_to_Suffer.jpeg
